  "notes": "CGSTL's high-resolution (Gaofen) series within the Jilin-1 program. eoPortal EO spec backfill (2026-07-09) from the Jilin / Gaofen Constellation mission page: the satellite table gives the Gaofen-03 platform at 0.75 m (JL-1-GF03D, improved) / 1 m (JL-1-GF03B), 17 km swath. Spectral bands and revisit not stated per-platform on the page, left null. Page last updated Mar 3, 2025. Bonus EO spec task (2026-07-13): re-read the same eoPortal page for the revisit field; it states the Gaofen-03 platforms' 'DailyVision' service delivers daily imaging with revisit ranging from 1.0 times per day at the equator to 2.1 times daily at 60 degrees latitude, a quantified figure, filled below. Spectral bands still not stated on the page for any Jilin-1 sub-series; left null rather than guessed. The page also states an aspirational future-constellation target of 138 satellites and 10-minute global revisit; that is a stated plan, not a current capability, and was not entered as a fact.",
